Third Department,

April, 1937.

(April 26, 1937.) The People of the State of New York, Respondent, v. Richard Hopkins, Appellant.

Motion to vacate and set aside order dismissing appeal, entered March 15, 1937, granted. Case ordered placed on calendar for term commencing May 4, 1937, and time for argument extended accordingly. Present — Hill, P. J., MeNamee, Crapser, Bliss and Heffeman, JJ.
